%% Diagram: Storage quota and eviction lifecycle across browsers
%% Type: stateDiagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false, 'flowchart': {'htmlLabels': false}}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> BestEffort: first write to IDB / Cache / OPFS
    BestEffort --> NearQuota: usage approaches origin quota
    NearQuota --> Eviction: quota exceeded -> QuotaExceededError
    BestEffort --> Eviction: group cap (~80%% disk) hit, browser evicts LRU origin
    BestEffort --> Persistent: navigator.storage.persist() granted
    Persistent --> Persistent: protected from automatic eviction (Chromium / Firefox)
    BestEffort --> SafariITP: 7 days of Safari use without site interaction
    Persistent --> SafariITP: persist() is a no-op in Safari
    SafariITP --> Eviction: ITP wipes script-writable storage
    Eviction --> [*]: re-sync from server on next visit
